    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Appearing commonly in China beginning in the eighth century CE, pagoda crypts are used to enshrine relics.  Frequently composed of a collection of separate chambers, the crypts sometimes contain murals which thematically complement their contents.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
